Preheat your #oven (for the tortillas) to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Drain the @Cannellini Beans{1%pack}. Quarter the @Lime{1/2%unit}.

Peel and grate the @Garlic{1%unit}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @Coriander{5%g}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Trim and thinly slice the @Scallion{2%unit}(trimmed and thinly sliced). Keep the white and green parts separate.

> TIP: Alternatively, you can warm your tortillas by dry-frying them in the pan.

Place a #pan over medium heat (no oil).

Once hot, dry-fry the @Central American Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} for ~{1%min}.

Add a drizzle of @Oil{to taste} to the pan and fry the garlic, beans and white portion of the scallion, ~{2-3%mins}.

Add the @Chopped Tomatoes{1%pack} and the juice of 2 lime wedges (double for 4p).

Mix well and simmer for ~{3-4%mins}.

Season to taste with @Salt{to taste}, @Pepper{to taste} and @Sugar{to taste}.

Crack your @Egg{2%unit} (1 per person) into the tomato sauce.

Cover the pan and cook for ~{6-8%mins}.

Remove the lid after ~{4%mins} and crumble over the @Goat's Cheese{100%g}(crumbled).

Simmer uncovered for the remaining cooking time to evaporate any excess water.

Meanwhile, pop half the @Tortilla{4%unit} (double for 4p) into the #oven to warm, ~{1-2%mins}.

Halve the @Avocado{1%unit} and remove the pit.

Cut the avocado into cubes while it's still in its skin, then use a #tablespoon to scoop out the chunks into a #serving bowl{}.

> TIP: If you prefer, warm the tortillas by dry-frying them in the pan for 1-2 mins.

Divide the white bean shakshouka between #bowls{}.

Garnish with the chopped coriander and green of the scallion.

Serve with the warm tortillas, avocado chunks and any remaining lime wedges.